The paper deals with sparse recovery using $\ell_1$ minimization, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The reweighted $\ell_1$ recovery algorithm proposed in the paper involves penalizing entries outside a set identified by the standard $\ell_1$ minimization step, which is related to signal processing (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the behavior of distributions at the origin, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and statistics (cs.SI).
